Steve_of_N21
London, UK3,348 contributions
Another of Barcelona’s neighbourhoods that is worth exploring.
May 2024 • Couples
This trip advisor listing is for the neighbourhood of Barceloneta, not the beach of Barceloneta which has its own Trip advisor listing.
This is the historic fisherman’s neighbourhood of Barcelona that somehow escaped the gentrification of the Barcelona Sea front for the 1992 Olympics. It is still a maze of narrow streets and although largely still a working-class district, in recent years it has built a reputation for quality sea food restaurants and tapas bars.
We had no problem walking here day or night, but the usual rules apply as it does for the Gothic Quarter and other tourist areas of Barcelona, just leave your expensive watches and handbags in the hotel room and your wallet tucked away and you will be fine.
Written June 4, 2024
